I had the same problem if i called .ToJson() in a nested OwnOne chain. 

```
var entityConfig= modelBuilder.Entity<EntityType>();
entityConfig.OwnsOne(x => x.Settings, nav =>
{
 nav.ToJson();
 nav.OwnsOne(x => x.InnerModel, innerNav => innerNav.ToJson() <----here);
});
```
After I deleted that part, there is no error, and my code is working properly.

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2828d34e-34f3-4c2b-b765-172d7cf824b5)

Hi @maumar,
If we add code like the one I shared below, won't it provide a solution? I could add the database properly when I bypassed this line in debug mode.

